---
<!-- Page header -->
<header class="page-header">
  <h1>Projects</h1>
</header>

<main>
  <div class="text-wrapper center" style="margin-top: 20px">
    <!-- Project link 1 -->
    <div class="page-text-block clearfix">
      <a href="/projects/rustbook">
        <div class="thumbnail">
          <img src="../assets/rust_logo.png" alt="image"/>
        </div>
        <h4>The Rust book</h4>
      </a>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 0.2em; color: #767676">Technologie used mdbook</p>
      <p>
        Rust is a systems programming language, that is focused on safety, speed, and concurrency.
        It achieves all these goals without having a garbage collector.
        It provides a number of compile-time safety checks that produce no runtime overhead, while eliminating all data races.
        This is the Dutch translation of the book. So have fun!
      </p>
    </div>
    <hr>
    <!-- Project link 2 -->
    <div class="page-text-block clearfix">
      <a href="/projects/website">
        <div class="thumbnail">
          <img src="../assets/jeroen_cops.png" alt"image"/>
        </div>
        <h4>The Website</h4>
      </a>
      <p style="font-size: 12px; margin-bottom: 0.2em; color: #767676">Technologie used Cobalt, HTML5, CSS3, Javascript, Jquery</p>
